Agency Name: Department of Health and Mental Hygiene
Resolution Description: The Department of Health and Mental Hygiene has sent official written notification to the Owner/Landlord warning them of potential violations and instructing them to correct the situation.  If the situation persists 21 days after your initial complaint, please make a new complaint.

Descriptor: No Certificate Of Occupancy/Illegal/Contrary To CO
Resolution Description: The Department of Buildings investigated this complaint and issued a violation.
The Police Department responded to the complaint and with the information available observed no evidence of the violation at that time.
The Department of Sanitation investigated this complaint and found no violation at the location.

The Taxi and Limousine Commission will send a confirmation letter in 14 days to confirm your complaint details. At the hearing you may be required to provide information regarding this complaint. Please note your Service Request number for future reference.
The Police Department responded to the complaint and took action to fix the condition.
The Department of Parks and Recreation has corrected the condition.
